    "Procedure": {
      "text": "Exact steps dependent on whether blood will be exchanged via an apheresis machine and specific model\nApheresis may require large-bore\ncentral venous catheter\n(e.g. HD line or pheresis catheter)\nIf no apheresis machine available:\nPlace at least two peripheral IVs\nSlowly remove 5-20mL of patient's blood\nReplace phlebotomized blood with warmed RBCs (or saline/albumin/plasma) in equal or greater amounts\nRepeat prior steps until desired amount transfused",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "central venous catheter",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Central_venous_catheter"
        }
      ]
    },
